====================================================================
itrans, avinash chopde <avinash@aczoom.com>   http://www.aczoom.com/itrans/
Files in the ITRANS/lib/fonts directory.

These fonts are not part of ITRANS - they have been collected
from various places on the Web, and are copyright by their
respective owners. A search on the Web with the font name will
yield more info.

These files are provided in one place just for convenience in
using ITRANS, they will be removed if the owners object to this
collection.

====================================================================
ITRANS 5.31 changes - dvng10 replaced by dvnb10. See top level CHANGES
file for details.
====================================================================

These are fonts that can be used on X11, PC, or Mac, for scripts that
are currently supported in ITRANS for direct text output.
Contain TeX and PostScript fonts too.

Note:
1) Most font files are in the correct format, you just need to install
them on your machine. Read your system manuals for instructions.
2) For the Mac, the font files are encoded in HQX format. To extract the
real font files, run the .hqx file through DeHQX or Stuffit-Expander.
3) For Unix/X11 systems, use the .pfa or .pfa PostScript Type 1 fonts.
Example fonts.scale file is available in ITRANS/lib directory.
4) Some fonts here are from packages available elsewhere, such as
TeluguTeX and Devnag. Use WWW search tools to find the locations where
you can get complete packages; both these are certainly available at all
TeX CTAN sites and their mirrors: ftp.cdrom.com, www.ctan.org, etc.

File Types:

*.mf	- TeX Metafont Source Files.
*.tfm	- TeX Metafont Font Metrics.
*.fd	- LaTeX font definiton files (LaTeX2e)
*.afm	- PostScript Type 1 Font Metrics.
*.pfa	- PostScript Type 1 Font - ASCII format
	- for X11R6 displays or PostScript printers. 
*.pfb	- PostScript Type 1 Font - Binary format.
	- for X11R6 displays or PostScript printers. 
*.ttf	- TrueType Font - For MS-Windows PCs.
*.hqx	- TrueType Font Suitcase - BinHex'ed - For Macintoshes.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

--------- Devnac PostScript Type III Font

devnac.ps		-- devnagari font description, in PostScript
			-- Type III PostScript Font

devnac.afm		-- the AFM (Adode Font Metric) file.
			-- referenced by the devn.ifm file, used by the
			-- itrans program

dnh.tfm
dnho.tfm
dnhrc.tfm
dnhre.tfm		-- the TFM files, used by TeX  (Devnagari Font)
			-- these correspond to the available fonts.
			-- PostScript font.

